The Premier Soccer league has charged AmaZulu Football Club for failing to provide adequate security personnel at their game against Mamelodi Sundowns. JOHANNESBURG- The Premier Soccer league has charged AmaZulu Football Club for failing to provide adequate security personnel at their game against Mamelodi Sundowns on Friday 2 March 2018 at the Princess Magogo Stadium, as required by the Compliance Manual. This is after a section of supporters at King Zwelithini Stadium threw objects on the field resulting in the game being stopped for about 10 minutes by the referee. AmaZulu will appear in front of the PSL disciplinary committee on 14 March 2018.